        <div type="recipe">
        <p> Take four Ounces of bitter Almonds, blanch and beat them as fine as you can; in beating them put in the Whites of four Eggs; then mix it up with sifted Sugar to a light Paste; roll them and lay them on Water Paper upon Tin Plates. Make the Paste so light that you may take it up with a Spoon. Bake them in a quick Oven. </p>
